<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,1094,1589]" box="[136,838,1094,1121]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">
<typeStatus box="[136,209,1095,1121]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">TYPE</typeStatus>
:— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Doll 1877: 329) Swallen (1948: 89)" authorityName="Swallen" authorityPageNumber="89" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Doll" baseAuthorityPageNumber="329" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[242,834,1094,1120]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Raddiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis box="[242,414,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Raddiella nana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Doll, J. C." box="[428,601,1094,1120]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="2" refId="ref24117" refString="Doll, J. C. (1877) Gramineae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis 2 (2). F. Fleischer, Munchen &amp; Leipzig, pp. 342." type="book chapter" year="1877">Döll 1877: 329</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Swallen, J. R." box="[616,834,1094,1120]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="56 - 115" refId="ref26893" refString="Swallen, J. R. (1948) Gramineae. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 75 (1): 56 - 115." type="journal article" year="1948">Swallen (1948: 89)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,1094,1589]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">
Plants delicate, tufted, forming low mats. Culms homomorphic, commonly decumbent, 
<quantity box="[1221,1323,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" unit="cm" value="20.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="1.0">1–40 cm</quantity>
tall, infra- and supranodal bands of trichomes absent, unbranched or branched, without thorns. Leaves not differentiated into culm leaves and foliage leaves. Leaf sheaths without fimbriae at the apex, translucent swelling absent, outer ligule absent, blades ovate-triangular or elliptical, midnerve not prominent. Synflorescences terminal and axillary, racemose, terminal synflorescence with male and female spikelets or more commonly strictly male, rarely female, axillary synflorescences barely exserted from the leaf sheaths; spikelets with filiform pedicels, solitary and unisexual, glumes 2 (female spikelets) or absent (male spikelets), anthecium smooth. Fruit a basic caryopsis, hilum punctiform or shortlinear, ca. ½ the length of caryopsis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="122" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,1094,1589]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1948" box="[189,298,1418,1444]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Raddiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,298,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Raddiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an herbaceous bamboo with eight species in Central and South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Kellogg, E. A." box="[1146,1306,1418,1445]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" refId="ref25159" refString="Kellogg, E. A. (2015) The Families and Genera of Vascular Plants Volume XIII. Flowering Plants Monocots: Poaceae. Springer International Publishing, Switzerland, 413 pp." type="book" year="2015">Kellogg 2015</bibRefCitation>
). It is mainly characterized by the decumbent culms, 
<quantity box="[578,674,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" unit="cm" value="23.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="6.0">6–40 cm</quantity>
tall, leaves ovate-triangular or elliptic and synflorescences racemose, terminal and axillary, with male and female spikelets usually arising from different synflorescences (
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Judziewicz, E. J." pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="928 - 941" refId="ref27951" refString="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Judziewicz, E. J. (1991) A Revision of Raddiella (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Olyreae). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 78 (4): 928 - 941." type="journal article" year="1991">Zuloaga &amp; Judziewicz 1991</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[372,443,1526,1552]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, five species occur in the Amazon, Caatinga, Cerrado and Mata Atlântica domains (Oliveira &amp; Oliveira 2020). In the Serra do Cachimbo, it is represented by three species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
